  pearls: ["Myasthenic crisis (weakness, respiratory failure) vs cholinergic crisis (too much medication, SLUDGE symptoms): both cause weakness but treatment is opposite", "Medication timing is critical: even 30 minutes late can cause significant symptom worsening", "Schedule meals 45-60 minutes after pyridostigmine when swallowing is strongest", "Many common medications worsen MG: aminoglycosides, beta-blockers, magnesium, certain anesthetics", "Ptosis and diplopia worse at end of day (fatigable weakness) is the hallmark pattern", "Keep atropine at bedside as antidote for cholinergic crisis from anticholinesterase overdose"],
